  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "On war-torn Typhos Prime, Colonel Schaeffer turns a thousand condemned Imperial Guardsmen into the Last Chancers, a penal strike force built by attrition and useful death. Lieutenant Kage, a former Cadian-trained soldier and Schaeffer's sharp-tongued survivor, narrates as squads are spent against an Ork incursion until only the hard core Schaeffer needs remains. A series-opener in Dirty-Dozen war-story mode: cynical first-person memoir, impossible-mission redemption, and a commander who treats salvation as another battlefield resource.",
